00:00:00.030 --> 00:00:03.120
Ziploc bags fantastic product but
unfortunately they're not

00:00:03.120 --> 00:00:06.870
one-size-fits-all, especially if you have
little gizmos gadgets or small trinket

00:00:06.870 --> 00:00:11.130
that you're trying to package up so much
bag for so little items so for this

00:00:11.130 --> 00:00:14.429
video I'm going to show you how you can
modify your Ziploc bags to be any size

00:00:14.429 --> 00:00:14.929
or shape you want. not sponsored by
Ziploc but I wish it was.

00:00:18.090 --> 00:00:21.720
now one quart freezer bags like these
are made of polyethylene which is a

00:00:21.720 --> 00:00:25.500
lightweight plastic polymer and it can
be melted which means if we took

00:00:25.500 --> 00:00:29.220
something long thin and made of metal
like these old metal coat hangers we

00:00:29.220 --> 00:00:32.910
should see theoretically be able to heat
them up and cut our bags in half now if

00:00:32.910 --> 00:00:35.370
you're wondering where you can even get
these metal coat hangers anymore just

00:00:35.370 --> 00:00:38.879
try stopping by your local dry cleaners
they'll probably give them to you for free if

00:00:38.879 --> 00:00:42.300
not four for a buck now we're also going
to need some kind of a cloth or a towel

00:00:42.300 --> 00:00:45.510
and you're going to want one that is not
super meaningful to you because it's

00:00:45.510 --> 00:00:48.000
going to get scorched it's going to get
burned and it's probably gonna get

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:51.390
covered in plastic as well I'm using one
of these shop rags and its purpose is

00:00:51.390 --> 00:00:54.480
just to provide a little bit of cushion
now what we want to do with our rag is

00:00:54.480 --> 00:00:57.180
set it down on the counter and fold it
up into thirds and this is just going to

00:00:57.180 --> 00:00:59.850
build up the height a little bit so it
provides a little more cushion next we

00:00:59.850 --> 00:01:03.120
want to take our ziplock bag and lay it
down onto the rag in the direction we

00:01:03.120 --> 00:01:05.640
want to make the cut now this is the
part where things start heating up a

00:01:05.640 --> 00:01:08.939
little bit so it's a good idea to have
some protective gloves maybe some safety

00:01:08.939 --> 00:01:12.030
glasses if you're into that and for a
heat source we're going to be using

00:01:12.030 --> 00:01:16.020
either a BBQ igniter or if you have one
a propane torch works great as well you

00:01:16.020 --> 00:01:18.810
can also use the open flame from a gas
range as well if you've got one of those

00:01:18.810 --> 00:01:22.049
in any case we just need some kind of a
hot open flame that we can concentrate

00:01:22.049 --> 00:01:26.850
on the bottom of our wire

00:01:26.850 --> 00:01:31.060
okay so our wire is heated up now we're
just going to drop it by the top line it

00:01:31.060 --> 00:01:36.190
over our bag and press it straight down
we can hold that in place grab the

00:01:36.190 --> 00:01:41.440
corner of our bag and just peel it right
up and as easy as that we now have a

00:01:41.440 --> 00:01:46.480
customized ziploc bag check that out
look how clean the edges are as well

00:01:46.480 --> 00:01:49.530
it's absolutely beautiful actually
worked out better than I thought and

