because we're using metal as it heats-up
it will have a tendency sometimes to

00:01:53.200 --> 00:01:57.130
bend upward so it's not a bad idea just
to bend it down and heat up first

00:01:57.130 --> 00:02:00.520
because then when you compress it will
press down into the material rather than

00:02:00.520 --> 00:02:04.450
having an awkward middle part that
doesn't get touch at all

